  "title": "Write the guide content",
  "body": "We need a very good guide for react-instantsearch that will explain basic and advanced concepts.\n\nParts that need to be written:\n- [ ] Introduction (what's react instantsearch)\n- [ ] Widgets (connected widgets to Algolia)\n- [ ] Connectors (HOC providing simple mechanism for controlling rendering)\n- [ ] Preselecting values (VirtualWidgets)\n- [ ] Configuring Algolia parameters (distinct use case)\n- [ ] Wrapping 3rd party libraries\n- [ ] Styling (CSS Class names only)\n- [ ] Creating a custom menu with manual items (#1062) \n- [ ] Conditionally displaying widgets\n- [ ] Url synchronisation (Only show it can be activated/deactivated)\n\nWe should leave out parts like creating your own widget, injecting state, passing a history etc. for now because those APIs are unstable and may well change in the future.\n",
